### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  PERSONAL FINANCE ASSISTANT — Full API Verification
###  Services: Auth · Upsert · Analytics · OCR/Bill Parser
###  Base URL: http://localhost:8080  (routed via API Gateway)
###
###  HOW TO USE:
###    1. Run the LOGIN request below (▶ next to # @name login)
###    2. All subsequent requests auto-populate {{login.response.body.*}}
###    3. Update @sampleImage / @samplePdf paths if needed
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@gatewayUrl  = http://localhost:8080
@userEmail   = testverify@gmail.com
@userPassword = tempPass123
@sampleImage = /home/vergin_jose/IdeaProjects/Personal-Finance-Assistant/requests/1.webp
@samplePdf   = /home/vergin_jose/IdeaProjects/Personal-Finance-Assistant/requests/Receipt.pdf

### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  AUTH — Login  (run this first)
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# @name login
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{userEmail}}",
  "password": "{{userPassword}}"
}

### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  UPSERT SERVICE
###  Base: /api/upsert
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### ── 1. CREATE — EXPENSE transaction ─────────────────────────────
###    Expected: 201 with generated id
# @name createExpense
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/create
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

{
  "userId": "{{login.response.body.userId}}",
  "name": "Swiggy Food Order",
  "amount": 450.00,
  "type": "EXPENSE",
  "currency": "INR",
  "expenseCategory": "FOOD_AND_DINING",
  "description": "Dinner order from Swiggy"
}

### ── 2. CREATE — INCOME transaction ──────────────────────────────
###    Expected: 201 with generated id
# @name createIncome
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/create
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

{
  "userId": "{{login.response.body.userId}}",
  "name": "Monthly Salary",
  "amount": 75000.00,
  "type": "INCOME",
  "currency": "INR",
  "incomeCategory": "SALARY",
  "description": "June 2026 salary credit"
}

### ── 3. CREATE — Idempotency key (send twice, same response) ─────
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/create
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}
X-Idempotency-Key: order-unique-key-abc123

{
  "userId": "{{login.response.body.userId}}",
  "name": "Netflix Subscription",
  "amount": 649.00,
  "type": "EXPENSE",
  "currency": "INR",
  "expenseCategory": "ENTERTAINMENT",
  "description": "Monthly Netflix plan"
}

### ── 4. UPDATE — modify the expense transaction ──────────────────
###    Expected: 200
PUT {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/update
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

{
  "id": "{{createExpense.response.body.id}}",
  "userId": "{{login.response.body.userId}}",
  "name": "Zomato Food Order",
  "amount": 520.00,
  "type": "EXPENSE",
  "currency": "INR",
  "expenseCategory": "FOOD_AND_DINING",
  "description": "Updated dinner order from Zomato"
}

### ── 5. LIST — all entries (paginated) ───────────────────────────
###    Expected: 200 with page of entries
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/entries?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}&page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 6. LIST — EXPENSE only ──────────────────────────────────────
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/entries?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}&type=EXPENSE&page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 7. LIST — INCOME only ───────────────────────────────────────
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/entries?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}&type=INCOME&page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 8. SEARCH — keyword search ─────────────────────────────────
###    Expected: 200 page containing matching entries
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/search?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}&query=salary&page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 9. SUMMARY — totals and net balance ────────────────────────
###    Expected: 200 with totalIncome, totalExpense, netBalance, totalCount
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/summary?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 10. GET SINGLE ENTRY BY ID ──────────────────────────────────
###     Expected: 200 with entry details
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/entries/{{createIncome.response.body.id}}?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 11. LIST — date range filter ───────────────────────────────
###     Expected: 200 page with entries in range
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/entries?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}&startDate=2026-01-01&endDate=2026-12-31&page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 12. PATCH AMOUNT — correct amount without full PUT ─────────
###     Expected: 200 with updated entry
PATCH {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/entries/{{createExpense.response.body.id}}/amount?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

{
  "amount": 999.99
}

### ── 13. CREATE RECURRING transaction ───────────────────────────
###     Expected: 201 with recurring=true, recurringPeriod=MONTHLY
# @name createRecurring
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/create
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

{
  "userId": "{{login.response.body.userId}}",
  "name": "Swimming Membership",
  "amount": 2000.00,
  "type": "EXPENSE",
  "currency": "INR",
  "expenseCategory": "HEALTHCARE",
  "description": "Monthly swimming membership",
  "recurring": true,
  "recurringPeriod": "MONTHLY"
}

### ── 14. LIST RECURRING entries ─────────────────────────────────
###     Expected: 200 array of all recurring transactions
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/recurring?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 15. EXPORT as CSV ───────────────────────────────────────────
###     Expected: 200 text/csv with Content-Disposition: attachment
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/entries/export?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 16. BULK DELETE ─────────────────────────────────────────────
###     Expected: 204 No Content
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/delete/bulk
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

{
  "userId": "{{login.response.body.userId}}",
  "ids": ["{{createExpense.response.body.id}}"]
}

### ── 17. SOFT DELETE — single entry ──────────────────────────────
###     Expected: 204 No Content
DELETE {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/delete/{{createIncome.response.body.id}}?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 18. Verify deleted entry gone from list ─────────────────────
###     Expected: 200 with totalElements not including deleted entry
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/entries?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}&page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 19. HEALTH CHECK ────────────────────────────────────────────
###     Expected: 200 {"status": "UP"}
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/upsert/health

### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  ANALYTICS SERVICE
###  Base: /api/analytics
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### ── 1. HEALTH CHECK ─────────────────────────────────────────────
###    Expected: 200 {"status": "UP", "service": "analytics-service"}
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/analytics/health
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 2. CATEGORY PIE CHART — all transactions ───────────────────
###    Expected: 200 with ChartData (labels + datasets)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/analytics/category-pie-chart?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 3. CATEGORY PIE CHART — EXPENSE only ───────────────────────
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/analytics/category-pie-chart?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}&transactionFilter=EXPENSE
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 4. CATEGORY PIE CHART — INCOME only ────────────────────────
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/analytics/category-pie-chart?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}&transactionFilter=INCOME
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 5. CATEGORY PIE CHART — date range (last month) ────────────
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/analytics/category-pie-chart?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}&startDate=2026-05-01T00:00:00&endDate=2026-05-31T23:59:59
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 6. TIMELINE CHART — monthly breakdown ──────────────────────
###    Expected: 200 with monthly time series data
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/analytics/timeline-chart?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}&timelineType=MONTHLY
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 7. TIMELINE CHART — weekly breakdown ───────────────────────
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/analytics/timeline-chart?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}&timelineType=WEEKLY
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 8. COMPREHENSIVE ANALYTICS — full report ───────────────────
###    Expected: 200 with summary + pie charts + timeline combined
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/analytics/comprehensive?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}&timelineType=MONTHLY
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 9. CUSTOM ANALYTICS — POST body ────────────────────────────
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/analytics/custom-analytics
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

{
  "userId": "{{login.response.body.userId}}",
  "timelineType": "MONTHLY",
  "startDate": "2026-01-01T00:00:00",
  "endDate": "2026-12-31T23:59:59"
}

### ── 10. TRANSACTION ENTRIES — paginated read-view ───────────────
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/analytics/transaction-entries?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}&page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 11. INCOME BY CATEGORY — SALARY ────────────────────────────
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/analytics/transactions/income-by-category?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}&incomeCategory=SALARY
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 12. TRANSACTIONS BY TYPE — EXPENSE ─────────────────────────
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/analytics/transactions/by-type?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}&type=EXPENSE
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 13. TRANSACTIONS BY TYPE — INCOME ──────────────────────────
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/analytics/transactions/by-type?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}&type=INCOME
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 14. TRANSACTIONS BY TYPE — EXPENSE with date range ─────────
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/analytics/transactions/by-type?userId={{login.response.body.userId}}&type=EXPENSE&startDate=2026-01-01&endDate=2026-12-31
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  OCR / BILL PARSER SERVICE
###  Base: /api/bill
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### ── 1. PROCESS IMAGE — upload a JPG/PNG/WEBP receipt ────────────
###    Expected: 200 with extracted financial data
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/bill/process/{{login.response.body.userId}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="receipt.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< {{sampleImage}}
------boundary--

### ── 2. PROCESS PDF — upload a PDF invoice ───────────────────────
###    Expected: 200 with extracted financial data
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/bill/process/{{login.response.body.userId}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="invoice.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< {{samplePdf}}
------boundary--

### ── 3. VALIDATION — missing file param ─────────────────────────
###    Expected: 400 Bad Request
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/bill/process/{{login.response.body.userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### ── 4. VALIDATION — wrong content type (JSON instead of multipart)
###    Expected: 400 Bad Request
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/bill/process/{{login.response.body.userId}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="data.json"
Content-Type: application/json

{"invalid": "file"}
------boundary--

### ── 5. UNAUTHENTICATED — no token ──────────────────────────────
###    Expected: 401 Unauthorized from API Gateway
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/bill/process/some-user-id
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="receipt.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< {{sampleImage}}
------boundary--
